# MeedyaSuite-core — Project Brief

## What Is This?

MeedyaSuite-core is the shared Rust core library for the MeedyaSuite product family.
It eliminates code duplication across MeedyaDL, MeedyaConverter, MeedyaManager, and
MeedyaDB by providing canonical type definitions and shared business logic.

## The Problem It Solves

Before this library, three active projects independently maintained:
- Audio/video codec enums (42+ audio codecs, 21+ video codecs)
- Container format definitions (36+ formats with extensions, MIME types)
- Metadata tag registries (TOML/JSON5-driven freeform atom definitions)
- Audio fingerprinting (AcoustID/Chromaprint)
- ReplayGain loudness analysis (EBU R128)
- MeedyaDB API client code
- Metadata provider integrations (MusicBrainz, TMDB, TheTVDB, etc.)

This duplication existed across Rust (MeedyaDL, MeedyaManager) and Swift
(MeedyaConverter), making changes error-prone and inconsistent.

## Crate Responsibilities

### meedya-codecs (Priority 1 — highest value)
The single source of truth for codec identity. Defines AudioCodec, VideoCodec,
SubtitleCodec, ContainerFormat, HdrFormat, SpatialAudioFormat enums with rich
metadata (FFmpeg names, lossless flags, compatibility matrices, classification).

### meedya-metadata (Priority 2)
Config-driven metadata tag system. TagRegistry loads tag definitions from TOML
(zero code changes to add tags). JSON path extraction engine for API responses.
CommonTag enum mapping standard field names across iTunes atoms, Vorbis Comments,
and ID3v2 frames.

### meedya-fingerprint (Priority 3)
Audio identification and loudness analysis. AcoustID API client with rate limiting.
ReplayGain analyzer using FFmpeg EBU R128 filter. Returns results only — consumers
handle tag writing via meedya-metadata.

### meedya-db (Priority 4)
Shared media record types (Track, Album, Artist). MeedyaDB API client for
api.meedya.tv/v1. DbExporter trait for multi-backend database export.

### meedya-providers (in progress)
Centralised metadata provider framework. MetadataProvider trait, capabilities
system, and shared implementations for services used across multiple apps
(MusicBrainz, TMDB, TheTVDB, AcoustID, Discogs, FanArt.tv, etc.).

## Integration Status

| Consumer | Status | Integration Path |
|----------|--------|-----------------|
| MeedyaDL (Rust/Tauri) | Pending | Direct Cargo git dependency |
| MeedyaManager (Rust) | Pending | Direct Cargo git dependency |
| MeedyaConverter (Swift) | Pending | Via bindings/swift C FFI |
| MeedyaDB (Swift) | Not started | Via bindings/swift C FFI |

## Key Dependencies

- serde (serialization), toml (config), thiserror (errors), strum (enum derive)
- reqwest + tokio (HTTP/async for API clients)
- lofty (planned: multi-format tag I/O)
- rusty-chromaprint + symphonia (planned: pure-Rust fingerprinting)
- chrono (timestamps), serde_json (JSON handling)

## Testing

55 unit tests across all crates. Run with `cargo test --workspace`.
All tests must pass before any push.
